FBIS4-38214 "drnes125_s_94002" FBIS-NES-94-125 Daily Report 29 Jun 1994 Iran Ministry Denies Holding Israeli Pilot Ministry Denies Holding Israeli Pilot LD2906055594 Tehran IRNA in English 0548 GMT 29 Jun 94 LD2906055594 Tehran IRNA English BFN [Text] Tehran, June 29, IRNA -- Iran's foreign Ministry Tuesday [28 June] categorically denied allegations made by the Zionist regime on the presence of an Israeli pilot in Iran and termed it as "sheer lie". Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and the Zionist regime's Air Force commander recently had claimed that Ron Arad, an Israeli pilot whose plane crashed in 1986 while bombarding south Lebanon, is in Iran. An informed source at the Foreign Ministry in a contact with IRNA categorically rejected the allegations and stressed "the Zionists were following other objectives by repeating such baseless and unfounded claims."
